{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"21061c98-e9f2-49c6-b393-ca55b26cb9de","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n   Use a version compatible with xunit 2.9.3 (check NuGet for the latest).\n\n3. **Add** the `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` output type to your project:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform makes your test project a standalone app).\n\n**Key differences after migration:**\n- Your test project becomes a self-contained executable\n- You can run it directly: `dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj`\n- `dotnet test` still works via the bridge property above\n\nThat's the core change — swap `xunit.runner.visualstudio` → `xunit.runner.mtp` and add the MSBuild property.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa1298b6-68e9-4419-a4da-1515daeb5576","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":368,"requestId":"6811:163A9A:780610:7F3163:6A044D48"},"id":"c92540d3-f84f-4831-9e24-be5de60e0e7d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:16.821Z","parentId":"fe0d0621-5c55-4484-a61f-f13516641800"}
